## Propagating Trace Context Across RabbitMQ

The issue is that RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You need to manually inject/extract them using `System.Diagnostics`.

### Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;
    if (Activity.Current.TraceStateString is { } state)
        props.Headers["tracestate"] = state;
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

### Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    ActivityContext parentContext = default;

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
    }

    // Start a linked activity that continues the upstream trace
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent Process",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext);  // <-- this links to Service A's trace

    // ... process the message
}
```

### Wire it up in `Program.cs` (both services)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(b => b
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

### Key points

- **`Activity.Current.Id`** is the W3C `traceparent` string (e.g., `00-traceId-spanId-01`).
- Passing it as `parentContext` on the consumer side stitches both services into one distributed trace.
- If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus, this propagation is built-in — you only need to register the library's `ActivitySource`.
